---
import ContactMe from "../components/ContactMe.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import SocialLinks from "../components/SocialLinks.astro";

// Static Images
import jsollyImage from "../images/jsolly.webp";
---

<Layout
    title="About John Solly"
    description="John Solly is a Division CTO and software engineer with experience spanning startups, Fortune 500s, federal agencies, and universities."
>
    <div
        class="about-section bg-subtle-dark-overlay-lvl-2 text-text rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 mx-auto"
    >
        <div class="profile flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center">
            <Image
                src={jsollyImage}
                alt="John Solly Avatar"
                class="rounded-full mb-4 md:mb-0 md:mr-6 w-48"
                loading="eager"
            />
            <div>
                <h1
                    class="text-2xl font-bold text-text leading-none tracking-tight"
                >
                    John Solly
                </h1>
                <p class="text-text leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
                    Division CTO & Software Engineer
                </p>
                <div class="social-links flex mt-3">
                    <SocialLinks imgLoading="eager" />
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="about-content mt-4 text-xl">
            <p>
                I've launched products used by millions and rooted out waste at
                federal agencies. From startups to Fortune 500s, research labs
                to DOGEâ€”I've seen how software gets built in every kind of
                organization.
            </p>
            <p>
                I have degrees in Geospatial Information Science and Geospatial
                Intelligence, but the real education has been shipping code as
                an IC, product owner, and consultant. Software development is a
                game, and I'm obsessed with playing it well. For the past
                decade, I deliberately turned down management tracks to stay
                technical. As Elon Musk says, "A cavalry captain should know how
                to ride a horse."
            </p>
            <p>
                Today, I'm a Division CTO at Leidos, leading digital
                modernization for federal health and benefits agencies. I advise
                on software architecture, evaluating technical partners, and
                finding the right solutions for our customers.
            </p>
            <p>
                Outside work, you can find me at a CrossFit gym, on a running
                trail, and in the kitchen cooking for my wife, Holiday, and son,
                Justice. There's usually an app I'm tinkering on, too.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <ContactMe />
</Layout>

<style>
    .about-content p + p {
        margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .about-section {
        background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        color: #171717;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
        box-shadow:
            0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1),
            0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        padding: 1.5rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .social-links {
        display: flex;
        margin-top: 0.75rem;
    }
</style>
